http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Militant%E2%80%99s-killing-sparks-clashes-in-Kashmir/article13996007.ece

South Kashmir’s Awantipora remained on the boil on Tuesday where clashes erupted between security forces and protesters following the killing of a local militant in an encounter.Lashkar-e-Toiba’s (LeT) Sajad Ahmad Bhat alias Peer was killed on Monday evening in an encounter with the security forces in Srinagar’s Zakura area. He was a resident of Awantipora’s Zewan area.Immediately after the funeral prayers, protesters clashed with the security forces and blocked the Srinagar-Jammu National Highway.Several protesters were injured in clashes near Sempora and Zewan areas.Protesters raised anti-India and pro-freedom slogans. Scores of tear-smoke shells were fired to control the situation.The slain militant was active since 2007. He first joined the Hizbul Mujahideen and later switched to the LeT.Meanwhile, locals told The Hindu that several youth were rounded up for participating in the funeral and later in the protests.